OS Platforms:
=============

	Unix/X11 (most brands, including 64-bit platforms)
	Win32    (Windows 95, 98, NT 4.0, Intel)
	
Hosting languages
=================

	SWI-Prolog	http://swi.psy.uva.nl/usr/jan/SWI-Prolog/
	Quintus Prolog	http://www.sics.se/quintus/
	SICStus Prolog  http://www.sics.se/ (foreseen shortly)
	
Documentation
=============

	# Programming in XPCE/Prolog
	Userguide to get you started.  Explains the interface, object
	model as well as creating new classes.  Provides `technique'
	sections, explaining how commonly encountered problems may
	be solved using XPCE.

	# Course Notes
	Document explaining roughly the same material as ``Programming
	in XPCE/Prolog'' in a condensed form.

	# Reference Manual
	Available using the built-in online help-system.  Includes
	various fully dynamic viewpoints to the reference material.


Licenses and Versions
=====================

	* Free option
	XPCE/SWI-Prolog for PC/Linux.  Fully functioning version
	distributed free of charge.  Binary only.  For personal
	and evaluation purposed only.

	* Evaluation
	XPCE/SWI-Prolog for Windows 95/98/NT, runs for 20 minutes.

	* Academic Unix license
	Complete version, distributed as source.  Compiles on most
	Unix platforms.  Binaries for SPARC/solaris are available
	as well.

	* Academic Windows license
	Complete version, distributed as binary only.

	* Commercial license
	Includes access to the full source (including the Windows
	binding and setup for Microsoft Visual C 5.0) and grands
	the right to distribute runtime applications free of charge.
	
	
